Had an early dinner here. Service was pretty good.  They have a nice patio area if you want to sit outside. I had 4 different tapas and they were all pretty good.I think stuffed red pepper with Tuna was my favorite.  I didn't love the croquette. I've had better.  Prices were very reasonable.  I had a glass of cava and 4 tapas for 11€I would definitely recommend checking it out and then stroll around the el born neighborhood because it's very cool.
